What should you do before using a microwave? Pay attention to these suggestions to keep you and everyone else safe. Cover your food in the microwave to prevent steam from rolling around the kitchen and potentially burning yourself. Clean the microwave regularly to prevent harmful bacteria from growing. Do not use a microwave together with a conventional oven to save space. Do not turn a microwave on that is unattended. Allow the microwave to finish cooking before opening the door. Do not put metal objects or containers in a microwave. Don't microwave liquids in a plastic container, this can cause a fire. Do not microwave plastic or containers with metal parts. Don't let containers overheat in the microwave. Don't microwave trash or uncooked food. Run the microwave with something inside it to prevent the motor from stopping. These suggestions can prevent accidents and maintain a safe home kitchen environment.
